beer.beer_description:
Ölen du håller i din hand är en American Pale Ale (APA). När denna skapades i USA användes den lokalt odlade humlen. Detta gav rikliga toner av citrus. Som brukligt är i USA snålades det inte heller med dom väldoftande råvarorna.
Mycket är helt enkelt mer! 

"Jag brinner för att göra öl med tydlig humlekaraktär. Här har jag arbetat med humlesorterna Cascade och Citra som ger en fräsch citruston."
- Daniel Granath, bryggmästare

items.badge_description: Looking for more kick than a session beer, but want to be able to stay for a few rounds? You have to keep it in the middle. That's 210 beers with an ABV greater than 5% and less than 10%. Try 5 more for Level 43!

There's beer in them thar hills! You're setting off on your journey through the world of beer, but be sure to take a little time to get to know each brewery as you go. That's a beer from 210 different breweries. Try 5 more for Level 43!

Fresh from the tap is one of the best ways to enjoy a beer. Just try to use a glass and not drink directly from the tap, as tempting as it may be. That's 180 checkins with the serving style of Draft. Try 5 more for Level 37!
Ahh, the trusty pale ale; crisp, refreshing, and always a good choice in a bind. That's 135 different Pale Ales or American Pale Wheats. Try 5 more for Level 28.
